<TEXT>
THE Herald already fields the strongest writing team in Scottish rugby
and tomorrow our unrivalled coverage is given added gloss with the first
of a regular series of columns from Kenny Logan.
Logan's dispatches in The Herald from the World Cup in South Africa
proved so popular that he returns to Herald Sport in a regular Saturday
morning slot which will address the burning issues of the day and
provide the inside track throughout this momentous season of cup and
Premiership rugby.
The addition of the Stirling County and Scotland winger to our rugby
team means that with Derek Douglas, Brian Meek, Bill McLaren and John
Beattie bringing you the latest news, features and analysis from the
world of rugby, Herald Sport offers a service second to none.
Tomorrow, in a Rugby Special to kick off the new season, The Herald
will profile the leading clubs and preview the action on the opening day
of an exciting new season. All this and Logan too.
When it comes to rugby there's only one distinctive voice. Don't miss
The Herald tomorrow.
</TEXT>
