<HEADLINE>Reid's new target is a ticket to tour in America</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>BILL JOHNSON</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>46</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976601233</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTLAND'S Dale Reid shot an opening three-under-par 69 to finish two
strokes off the lead in the Wilkinson Sword English Open at The
Oxfordshire Club yesterday, then announced she was heading for the
United States. Reid has entered for the preliminary test at Mission
Hills in California next week when she will attempt to earn a place at
the qualifying school for the LPGA Tour.
''I still believe that I can win again and I want to get my record
number of wins back from Laura Davies. Going to America will set me
another goal,'' she said.
She added: ''I feel that my game has become stagnant. In America the
weather makes for more consistent conditions and I want to prove to
myself that I can still play golf.
''To do that I need to play more tournaments. Ideally I would like to
become an international member of the LPGA like Laura (Davies) and
divide my time between America and Europe.''
Reid three-putted three times in her 69 which also included a penalty
drop from water at the eleventh. But there were six birdies.
The leader is Wendy Dicks from Essex, whose 67 is her best start in
three years on the Tour. She is one ahead of Lancashire's Diane Barnard,
who had three 2s in four holes from the short fifth which she followed
with eagles at the par-4 sixth and eighth holes where, in turn, she
holed a wedge and No.6-iron second shots. Leading scores (British or
Irish unless stated):
67 -- W Dicks.
68 -- D Barnard.
69 -- D Reid, F Dassu (Italy).
70 -- K Speak, C Louw (S Africa), M Bertilskold (Sweden), S Mendiburu
(France), J Morley, C Hjalmarsson (Sweden), P Grice-Whittaker.
Others included: 72 -- L Davies. 0 73 -- M McKinlay. 74 -- J Forbes, L
Irvine. 75 -- T Craik, G Stewart. 77 -- C Panton-Lewis. 81 -- J Kinloch.
