<TEXT>
SCOTLAND coach Jim Love watched Stenhousemuir seamer Graeme Gardner
bowl the B team to victory yesterday, then admitted: ''He was only my
sixth choice pace bowler.''
Gardner ripped the heart out of Yorkshire Cricket Academy's batting
line-up to give the Scots victory by 147 runs in the three-day match at
Bradford.
Iain Philip's side set up their win with a brisk batting show during
the morning session. Grange batsman Cordon McGurk top-scored with 87,
including eleven 4s, and he had fine support from Carlton's Jim Govan,
who hit 61.
But once again Ayrshire's Drew Parsons stole the show with a thrilling
knock of 48 in double-quick time to let Philip declare at lunch, leaving
the Tykes 300 to win. Scoreboard:
