<TEXT>
THE Scottish side for the Home International matches, to be played at
Royal Portrush from September 20 to 22, yesterday was topped up to its
playing strength of 11 by the addition of Craig Watson (East
Renfrewshire) and Roger Beames (Wick). The nine others were chosen
earlier this month.
Watson, an established team member, has this season won the
Craigmillar Park Open and lost in the final defending his Mid Amateur
title. Beames, a semi-finalist in the Amateur Championship, convinced
the selectors with his runaway victory for the North of Scotland title
last weekend. Beames joins Michael Brooks and Alan Turnbull as newcomers
to the event. Team:
Roger Beames (Wick), Michael Brooks (Carluke), Stephen Gallacher
(Bathgate), Barclay Howard (Cochrane Castle), Simon MacKenzie (West
Linton), Hugh McKibbin (Troon Welbeck), Graham Rankin (Palacerigg), Alan
Reid (Barassie), Gordon Sherry (Barassie), Alan Turnbull (Innerleithen),
and Craig Watson (East Renfrewshire). Captain -- Colin Dalgleish.
Reserves -- Steven Young (Inverallochy) and Ewan Forbes (Nairn).
* JOHN Daly, the Open champion, and Laura Davies -- the longest
hitters in men's and women's professional golf -- are to meet in a Skins
game in Australia next February.
Davies has accepted an invitation to play alongside Daly, Tom Watson
and Australian Peter Senior at Sanctuary Cove, Queensland. ''We are all
playing from the same tees, so it will be a real challenge,'' said
Davies.
* GARRY Harvey won the Ben Pro-Am at Royal Burgess, Edinburgh,
yesterday with a five-under-par 63. He didn't drop a shot and carded
four birdies in six holes from the turn, as well as a birdie at the
second. Leading scores:
63 -- G Harvey (Grangemouth). 64 -- G Law (Uphall). 65 -- K Walker
(Kings Links); R Weir (Cowal), S Craig (Dunfermline). 66 -- F Mann
(Musselburgh), I Young (Braidhills), D Scott (Letham Grange). Team: 55
-- K Logan (Port Royal DR), C Bullock, S Carter, C Frood.
