<HEADLINE>Glass attack</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976601254</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A WOMAN who slashed her step-sister with a broken glass when they fell
out after a family funeral was put on probation for a year at Edinburgh
Sheriff Court yesterday. Karen Renton, 28, of 41/12 Caledonian Crescent,
Edinburgh, had been found guilty of assaulting Donna Young on October
24, 1994.
