<DOCNO>GH950901-000036</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950901-000036</DOCID>
<DATE>950901</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Deadline passes for Scotsman bids</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>23</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976601256</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BIDS closed yesterday for offers to take over The Scotsman and the
other Thomson Corporation newspapers in Scotland.
On the market are the Aberdeen Journals group, The Scotsman and its
Edinburgh stablemates, the Evening News and Scotland on Sunday.
It is believed that Caledonian Newspapers Limited, publishers of The
Herald and Evening Times, has successfully raised the relevant finance
to back its bid.
A Thomson Corporation spokeswoman said it would be making no comment
on how many bids had been lodged.
Among the interested parties are a Scottish-based consortium led by
lawyer Ross Harper, Associated Newspapers, publishers of the Daily Mail,
and a private London-based consortium.
The papers were put on the market by The Thomson Corporation seven
weeks ago after it had sold its English-based titles to Trinity
Holdings.
</TEXT>
