<TEXT>
THOSE in the habit of reading John Macleod could be forgiven for
concluding that he had never heard of the God who loves and is love, or
that he was ignorant of Jesus's greatest command -- to love.
His article, Barrymore goes down the road to destruction, showed
breathtaking ignorance of human sexuality, and many Christians would
find it both offensive and embarrassing, preferring instead to take the
life and teaching of Jesus more seriously.
Paul Middleton,
362 Castlemilk Road,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
