<HEADLINE>irthday cake on Mount Igman</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>11</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976601316</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A TEENAGER, who was the youngest UN soldier in Bosnia when his
regiment was sent to protect the Sarajevo area, celebrated his
eighteenth birthday on the outskirts of the war-torn city yesterday.
Private Lee Symons, a machine gunner with the Exeter-based Devon and
Dorset Regiment, read his cards while dug in on Mount Igman.
On his first birthday away from home, Private Symons tucked into an
iced cake made by his mum -- complete with a silver key of the door --
and opened a present of a new shirt.
</TEXT>
