<HEADLINE>Taste of home for Gunners</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>11</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976601317</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HIGHLAND soldiers can look forward to a taste of home next week. Four
hampers of goodies, from whisky to oatcakes, are going to the 19th
Regiment Royal Artillery, better known as the Highland Gunners.
Money for the hampers was raised at this year's Inverness Tattoo plus
donations from local busineses. The Highland Gunners have been regulars
at the tattoo but had to drop out this year when they were sent to
Bosnia as part of the UN's peace-keeping force.
</TEXT>
