<DOCID>GH950901-000101</DOCID>
<DATE>950901</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Miners killed by gas blast</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976601321</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MADRID: Fourteen miners were killed yesterday when an explosion ripped
through two galleries 1500ft underground in northern Spain. Two men
survived the blast at the privately-owned San Nicolas mine at Mieres,
near Oviedo in the coal-mining region of Asturias.
It is believed that a build-up of firedamp gas caused the explosion,
which was Spain's worst mining accident in 20 years. Unions called a
national strike today in all Spanish mines in tribute to the dead.
</TEXT>
