<DOCNO>GH950901-000104</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950901-000104</DOCID>
<DATE>950901</DATE>
<HEADLINE>No Headline Present</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>976601324</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Chief Minister of the Indian state of Punjab and 12 other people
were killed in a massive car bomb blast outside the state government
offices in Chandigarh today.
Beant Singh, a Sikh from the ruling Congress party who had been Chief
Minister for three years, was blown apart.
There was no immediate indication of who was behind the blast, in
which at least 30 people were injured.
Singh was always surrounded by commando bodyguards, five of whom died
in the blast along with two aides. He was known for his tough methods in
putting down a revolt by fellow Sikhs campaigning for an independent
Khalistan.
</TEXT>
