<HEADLINE>Pound of flesh</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976601338</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TEHRAN: Iran's Supreme Court has upheld a manslaughter conviction
against a former MP and ordered him to pay blood money, or diyeh, for
killing a man in an argument over shooting partridges. Under Iran's
Islamic law, diyeh is one of the following or their value as agreed by
the two sides -- 100 camels, 1000 sheep, 200 silk dresses, 1000 gold
coins, or 10,000 silver coins.
